
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-tcpm-early-rexmt-04.txt'>
    <title>"Early Retransmit for TCP and SCTP", Mark Allman, Konstantin Avrachenkov, Urtzi Ayesta, Ethan Blanton, Per Hurtig</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-tcpm-early-rexmt-04.txt</link>
    <description>This document proposes a new mechanism for TCP and SCTP that can be used to recover lost segments when a connection's congestion window is small.  The "Early Retransmit" mechanism allows the transport to reduce, in certain special circumstances, the number of duplicate acknowledgments required to trigger a fast retransmission.  This allows the transport to use fast retransmit to recover segment losses that would otherwise require a lengthy retransmission timeout.</description>
    <dc:date>2010-01-26T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
